The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 25 (PTI): India has banned import of milk and other dairy products from China for three months following reports of deaths because of contamination in whitener in the neighbouring country.          
	Reports suggest at least four infants died in China after consuming the contaminated milk. Melamine, used for making plastics and fertiliser, was found in infant formula and other milk products of 22 Chinese dairy firms. The dangerous chemical can cause kidney failure.                  
	 Mumbai: A court has acquitted a person arrested for drink-driving this February. The judge accepted Rohan Nikams argument that he was convicted solely on the basis of the readings of the breath analyser and his blood test report was not considered.                  
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): A case was registered against three trekking agencies on Wednesday for allegedly sending trekkers to Kalindi Badrinath despite unfavourable weather in the higher reaches of the Himalayas.                  
	 Calcutta (PTI): The West Bengal government on Thursday decided to recruit for all vacant posts through the state Public Service Commission. The decision will not cover the state government undertakings, corporations, municipalities, panchayats and government-sponsored schools and colleges.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A Blueline bus caught fire in Delhi on Thursday. Nobody was hurt in the accident, which took place at 2.30pm near Jantar Mantar on route no. 181 from Jahangirpuri to Nizamuddin. The fire started from the drivers cabin.                   
	 Raipur (PTI): The wife of an IAS officer has been arrested after she hurled expletives at a judge of a local court in Raipur. The altercation began after Romi Singh allegedly ignored judge Sangita Tiwaris warning to speak in a lower tone on her cellphone.                                                                                                                         
